feat(hy3): dump_tree workspace arg + dump_all dispatcher

Extends hl.plugin.hy3.dump_tree("<path>"[, ws])() with an optional
workspace id: no ws (or ws <= 0) dumps the active workspace as before; a
positive ws dumps that workspace's tree (getWorkspaceByID +
hy3InstanceForWorkspace), so a consumer can read a non-active workspace
without switching to it.

Also adds hl.plugin.hy3.dump_all("<path>")() -- writes every live hy3
workspace's tree as a JSON array sorted by workspace id (iterating the
g_hy3Instances registry). Unblocks `hy3-layout show --wk N` and `--wk
all` with no workspace switch / flicker. The per-workspace object schema
is unchanged ({"workspace":N,"root":<node>}); dump_all wraps them in an
array.
